The paper deals with pricing mechanisms in large markets with multiple buyers and a single seller, which is a classic topic in game theory and mechanism design (cs.GT). The paper also discusses efficient algorithms for pricing, which falls under the category of algorithms and complexity (cs.DS). The paper's focus on maximizing social welfare suggests that it may also be relevant to multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and economics and computation (cs.EC). Finally, the use of buyer valuations and utility maximization suggests that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
